FBIS4-18876 "drweu070__a94029" FBIS-WEU-94-070-A Daily Report 12 April 1994 ANNEX Germany Sees Relations Put on `New Basis' Sees Relations Put on `New Basis' AU1104203294 Hamburg DPA in German 1520 GMT 11 Apr 94--FOR OFFICIAL USE ONLY AU1104203294 Hamburg DPA German BFN [Text] [No dateline as received] -- According to [Ukrainian Defense Minister] Radezki, Germany and Ukraine have put their relations on a new basis with military cooperation. After the signing of a joint statement, Radezki stressed to journalists that Ukraine is "extremely interested" in equal integration into all-European structures. With NATO's Partnership for Peace initiative, new European security is being created. [German Defense Minister] Ruehe explained that Ukraine is an "important partner" for Germany. The FRG wants to provide aid to Kiev also within the framework of Partnership for Peace. Ukrainian officers are to be trained in Germany.
